SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 631
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Mike Keeney to
the state university board of the University of
Memphis.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-101, provides for the governance
of the University of Memphis by a state university board; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, provides that the governor
shall appoint six members to the state university board of the University of Memphis; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, further provides that at least
three of the gubernatorial appointees shall be alumni of the institution for which they are serving;
and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Mike Keeney to the state university board
of the University of Memphis for a term that will expire on June 30, 2031; and
WHEREAS, Mike Keeney is a lawyer and an active member of the Memphis business
community who has practiced law in the city since 1993; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Keeney gives back to his community through his service as Chair of the
Memphis-Shelby County Airport Authority and the Chairman's Circle of the Memphis Chamber
of Commerce and a member of the Tennessee Sports Wagering Commission, Douglas Henry
Tennessee State Museum Commission, Tennessee Transportation Modernization Board, and
the University of Memphis Board of Trustees; and
WHEREAS, an active community volunteer, Mr. Keeney serves on several nonprofit
boards and the executive committee of the Tennessee Business Leadership Council; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Keeney is a 1992 graduate of the University of Tennessee in Knoxville
College of Law and received a Bachelor of Arts degree in Philosophy from Lambuth College in
in 1988; and
SJR0631
011636
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, provides that each member
appointed by the governor to the state university board of the University of Memphis shall be
subject to confirmation by the senate and the house of representatives; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby confirm the appointment of Mike Keeney
to the state university board of the University of Memphis for a term that will expire on June 30,
2031.
